  - 803
By: Nicholas of Cusa
---
Rest is unity, in which all movement is contained, for on close examination
movement is seen to be rest drawn out in an orderly series. ... Unity is
convertible with eternity, for there cannot be more than one Eternal. God,
therefore, envelops all in the sense that all is found in Him.
